FBIS3-43446 "drafr005_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Police-PAC Clash Leaves 1 Dead; 6 Wounded 6 Jan MB0601205094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 2000 GMT 6 Jan 94 MB0601205094 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] A 13-year-old PAC [Pan-Africanist Congress] member has been shot dead and six others including a six-year-old child have been wounded in clashes between police and a group of PAC members in Guguletu in the Cape Peninsula a short while ago. The trouble flared after police arrived at a PAC meeting in the township and took away nine youths for questioning in connection with the Heidelberg tavern attack. PAC executive member Patricia de Lille and other senior PAC officials are locked in talks with high-ranking policemen to discuss the situation, a situation which is said to be extremely tense.
